<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,1057,1123,1150]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">
Confusion of two new species in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Razowski, 2012" authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[680,1057,1123,1150]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[680,856,1123,1149]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Gnathodracon</emphasis>
Razowski, 2012
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="595" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[151,1437,1123,1770]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">
Razowski (2012) proposed the new genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[636,791,1157,1181]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[636,791,1157,1181]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Gnathodracon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which he placed five new species. Unfortunately, the descriptions and illustrations of two of the species are mixed. When comparing specimens with the descriptions and figures in Razowski’s paper, it is clear that Razowski figured the adults of one species under one name and its genitalia under another name. Even though the captions to the figures indicate otherwise, the adults in figures 14 and 15 belong to the species described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[420,563,1296,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculina">
<emphasis box="[420,563,1296,1320]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. orbiculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(also the name indicates this), and the adult in figure 11 belongs to the species described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[295,470,1330,1354]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lukimayumbe">
<emphasis box="[295,470,1330,1354]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. lukimayumbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(e.g. “wing rubbed”). The figures of the male genitalia of the two species are labelled correctly. There is further confusion because under the description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[887,1027,1365,1389]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculina">
<emphasis box="[887,1027,1365,1389]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. orbiculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, it is stated: “Wing span of one female 
<quantity box="[151,232,1401,1424]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" unit="mm" value="16.0">16 mm</quantity>
,”, but later it is stated: “Female genitalia unknown.”, and in the last line states: “ 
<typeStatus box="[1097,1203,1401,1424]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Paratypes</typeStatus>
<docIssue box="[1210,1223,1401,1424]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">3</docIssue>
identically labelled males.” The female genitalia on slide 00401 (figure 9, labelled as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[855,1026,1434,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lukimayumbe">
<emphasis box="[855,1026,1434,1458]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. lukimayumbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) actually belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[1240,1380,1434,1458]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculina">
<emphasis box="[1240,1380,1434,1458]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. orbiculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The correct associations of the numbers in Razowski’s paper are as follows: figures 2, 9, 14 and 15 belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[1294,1436,1469,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculina">
<emphasis box="[1294,1436,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. orbiculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and figures 5 and 11 belong to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[485,657,1504,1528]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lukimayumbe">
<emphasis box="[485,657,1504,1528]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. lukimayumbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The mistake in Razowski’s publication stems from switching the labels belonging to the 
<typeStatus box="[343,447,1539,1562]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">holotypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[490,635,1538,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculina">
<emphasis box="[490,635,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. orbiculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[695,870,1538,1562]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lukimayumbe">
<emphasis box="[695,870,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. lukimayumbe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. To prevent future confusion we present corrected figures of the adults, labels, and genitalia of the 
<typeStatus box="[699,803,1574,1597]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">holotypes</typeStatus>
of the two species and the single female 
<typeStatus box="[1278,1370,1574,1597]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">paratype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. orbiculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[276,378,1609,1632]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="1.[151,258,1680,1702]" captionTargetBox="[154,1436,182,1654]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,182,1657]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Gnathodracon spp. 1 – 3: Gnathodracon lukimayumbe Razowski, 2012; 1. — Holotype ♂, 2. — Holotype labels, — Holotype labels, 3. — Holotype male genitalia; 4 – 9: Gnathodracon orbiculina Razowski, 2012; 4. — Holotype ♂, 5. — Holotype labels, 6. — Holotype male genitalia, 7. — Paratype ♀, 8. — Paratype labels, 9. — Paratype female genitalia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1048479/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Figs. 1–9</figureCitation>
). The labels of the 
<typeStatus box="[580,684,1609,1632]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">holotypes</typeStatus>
have now been placed under the correct specimens, and the material is deposited in the Royal Museum for Central Africa (
<collectionCode box="[699,783,1643,1666]" country="Belgium" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/ee3x-fpgk" name="Royal Museum for Central Africa" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">RMCA</collectionCode>
), Tervuren, 
<collectingCountry box="[910,1005,1643,1666]" name="Belgium" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Belgium</collectingCountry>
. During a recent visit (
<date box="[1247,1428,1643,1666]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" value="2017-10-01">
01 October 
<docYear box="[1373,1428,1643,1666]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">2017</docYear>
</date>
) by the authors to the Institute of Systematics and Evolution of Animals, Polish Academy of Sciences, Krakow (
<collectionCode box="[1338,1402,1678,1701]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">ISEA</collectionCode>
), it was observed that 
<typeStatus box="[357,459,1713,1736]" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[500,643,1712,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculina">
<emphasis box="[500,643,1712,1736]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">G. orbiculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were placed under the correct label, “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Razowski" authorityYear="2012" box="[1069,1345,1712,1736]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Gnathodracon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="595" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbiculina">
<emphasis box="[1069,1345,1712,1736]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="595">Gnathodracon orbiculina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, in the collection. This confirms that the information given in the present paper is correct.
</paragraph>
